  "root_text": {
    "snp4.1:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 4.1 ",
    "snp4.1:0.2": "Kāmasutta ",
    "snp4.1:1.1": "Kāmaṁ kāmayamānassa, ",
    "snp4.1:1.2": "tassa ce taṁ samijjhati; ",
    "snp4.1:1.3": "Addhā pītimano hoti, ",
    "snp4.1:1.4": "laddhā macco yadicchati. ",
    "snp4.1:2.1": "Tassa ce kāmayānassa, ",
    "snp4.1:2.2": "chandajātassa jantuno; ",
    "snp4.1:2.3": "Te kāmā parihāyanti, ",
    "snp4.1:2.4": "sallaviddhova ruppati. ",
    "snp4.1:3.1": "Yo kāme parivajjeti, ",
    "snp4.1:3.2": "sappasseva padā siro; ",
    "snp4.1:3.3": "Somaṁ visattikaṁ loke, ",
    "snp4.1:3.4": "sato samativattati. ",
    "snp4.1:4.1": "Khettaṁ vatthuṁ hiraññaṁ vā, ",
    "snp4.1:4.2": "gavāssaṁ dāsaporisaṁ; ",
    "snp4.1:4.3": "Thiyo bandhū puthu kāme, ",
    "snp4.1:4.4": "yo naro anugijjhati. ",
    "snp4.1:5.1": "Abalā naṁ balīyanti, ",
    "snp4.1:5.2": "maddantenaṁ parissayā; ",
    "snp4.1:5.3": "Tato naṁ dukkhamanveti, ",
    "snp4.1:5.4": "nāvaṁ bhinnamivodakaṁ. ",
    "snp4.1:6.1": "Tasmā jantu sadā sato, ",
    "snp4.1:6.2": "Kāmāni parivajjaye; ",
    "snp4.1:6.3": "Te pahāya tare oghaṁ, ",
    "snp4.1:6.4": "Nāvaṁ sitvāva pāragūti. ",
    "snp4.1:6.5": "Kāmasuttaṁ paṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp4.1:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 4.1 ",
    "snp4.1:0.2": "Sensual Pleasures ",
    "snp4.1:1.1": "If a mortal desires sensual pleasure ",
    "snp4.1:1.2": "and their desire succeeds, ",
    "snp4.1:1.3": "they definitely become elated, ",
    "snp4.1:1.4": "having got what they want. ",
    "snp4.1:2.1": "But for that personage in the throes of pleasure, ",
    "snp4.1:2.2": "aroused by desire, ",
    "snp4.1:2.3": "when those pleasures fade, ",
    "snp4.1:2.4": "it inflicts them like an arrow strike. ",
    "snp4.1:3.1": "One who, being mindful, ",
    "snp4.1:3.2": "avoids sensual pleasures ",
    "snp4.1:3.3": "like side-stepping a snake’s head, ",
    "snp4.1:3.4": "transcends attachment to the world. ",
    "snp4.1:4.1": "There are many objects of sensual desire: ",
    "snp4.1:4.2": "fields, lands, and gold; cattle and horses; ",
    "snp4.1:4.3": "slaves and servants; women and relatives. ",
    "snp4.1:4.4": "When a man lusts over these, ",
    "snp4.1:5.1": "the weak overpower him ",
    "snp4.1:5.2": "and adversities crush him. ",
    "snp4.1:5.3": "Suffering follows him ",
    "snp4.1:5.4": "like water in a leaky boat. ",
    "snp4.1:6.1": "That’s why a personage, ever mindful, ",
    "snp4.1:6.2": "should avoid sensual pleasures. ",
    "snp4.1:6.3": "Give them up and cross the flood, ",
    "snp4.1:6.4": "as a bailed-out boat reaches the far shore. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp4.1:2.1": "kāmayānassa → kāmayamānassa (si, mr) ",
    "snp4.1:3.3": "Somaṁ → so imaṁ (si, pts-vp-pli1) ",
